---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Blog — Perqed" activeNav="blog">

  <section class="blog-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Blog</p>
      <h1 class="header-title">Build log</h1>
      <p class="header-desc">
        Milestones, deep-dives, and lessons from building an autonomous proof engine.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="blog-list">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="post-card">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <time>March 21, 2026</time>
          <span class="tag">number-theory</span>
          <span class="tag">lean4</span>
          <span class="tag">data</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="post-title">
          <a href="/blog/goldbach-geodesic-chasm/">The Multiplicative-Additive Chasm</a>
        </h2>
        <p class="post-excerpt">
          Why hyperbolic geometry gives powerful control over prime products but says almost
          nothing about prime sums — and what 10⁶ data points reveal about the boundary
          of Goldbach's conjecture.
        </p>
        <a class="read-link" href="/blog/goldbach-geodesic-chasm/">Read post →</a>
      </article>
      <article class="post-card">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <time>March 19, 2026</time>
          <span class="tag">architecture</span>
          <span class="tag">rag</span>
          <span class="tag">llm</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="post-title">
          <a href="/blog/librarian-and-skill-injection/">The Engine Reads Mathematics Now</a>
        </h2>
        <p class="post-excerpt">
          From graph coloring to universal domains: how we taught Perqed to read academic papers,
          inject mathematical skills, and escape the read-only $bunfs trap.
        </p>
        <a class="read-link" href="/blog/librarian-and-skill-injection/">Read post →</a>
      </article>
      <article class="post-card">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <time>March 18, 2026</time>
          <span class="tag">engineering</span>
          <span class="tag">llm</span>
          <span class="tag">ramsey</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="post-title">
          <a href="/blog/teaching-the-architect-to-panic/">Teaching the ARCHITECT to Panic</a>
        </h2>
        <p class="post-excerpt">
          Seven hours of search with a dead planner — the Proof DAG was silently failing on every
          pivot due to a backtick, and falling back to naive SA. Here's how we gave the engine
          multi-stage basin escape, escalating LLM creativity, 25 mathematical proof SKILLs,
          and Math-First Triage.
        </p>
        <a class="read-link" href="/blog/teaching-the-architect-to-panic/">Read post →</a>
      </article>

      <article class="post-card">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <time>March 16, 2026</time>
          <span class="tag">engineering</span>
          <span class="tag">z3</span>
          <span class="tag">architecture</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="post-title">
          <a href="/blog/how-we-got-our-stack/">We Got Stuck, and Then We Had an Architecture</a>
        </h2>
        <p class="post-excerpt">
          SA hit E=12 and wouldn't move. Instead of tuning hyperparameters, we asked the
          right question: does a solution even exist? Z3 answered in seconds — UNSAT — and
          we almost threw the result away. This is the story of how a stuck search run
          became a solver stack.
        </p>
        <a class="read-link" href="/blog/how-we-got-our-stack/">Read post →</a>
      </article>

      <article class="post-card">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <time>March 15, 2026</time>
          <span class="tag">engineering</span>
          <span class="tag">simulated-annealing</span>
          <span class="tag">lean4</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="post-title">
          <a href="/blog/torus-decomposition/">Finding Needles in a 6<sup>215</sup> Haystack</a>
        </h2>
        <p class="post-excerpt">
          The paper proves the m=4 and m=6 torus decompositions are correct.
          This post covers what the paper skips: the energy function bug, the
          12× incremental speedup, and the TypeScript-to-Lean handoff.
        </p>
        <a class="read-link" href="/blog/torus-decomposition/">Read post →</a>
      </article>

      <article class="post-card">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <time>March 14, 2026</time>
          <span class="tag">milestone</span>
          <span class="tag">lean4</span>
          <span class="tag">deepseek-r1</span>
          <span class="tag">prover-v2</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="post-title">
          <a href="/blog/first-autonomous-proof/">Two Autonomous Proofs, Two Paradigms</a>
        </h2>
        <p class="post-excerpt">
          Two models prove n + m = m + n in Lean 4 — R1:8B as a strategist (77s, 1 shot) and
          Prover-V2 as a speedrunner (33s, 7 iterations). Plus: the quantization trap.
        </p>
        <a class="read-link" href="/blog/first-autonomous-proof/">Read post →</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .blog-header {
    padding: 80px 0 40px;
  }

  .header-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .header-desc {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    max-width: 460px;
  }

  .blog-list {
    padding-bottom: 80px;
  }

  .post-card {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 36px 0;
  }

  .post-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .post-meta time {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    background: var(--accent-purple-subtle);
    color: var(--accent-purple);
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .post-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .post-title a {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .post-title a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .post-excerpt {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  .read-link {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .read-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .blog-header { padding: 48px 0 24px; }
    .header-title { font-size: 1.9rem; }
  }
</style>
